16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
21 Services, in cooperation with the Oklahoma State Department of
22 Education, shall solicit proposals for, and if funds are available,
23 make grants to local boards of education for the establishment of
24 pilot programs that utilize artificial intelligence (AI) software as
Req. No. 11535 Page 1

1 a sa fety tool to monitor school issued devices. The proposals for
2 the pilot programs shall create an AI inference engine that provides
3 school districts with precise insights into student safety and
4 readiness to learn and utilize CIPA complaint web filtering and
5 other existing and approved data channels to produce a report
6 concerning a student's readiness to learn, interests, general well-
7 being, and other multi-tiered systems of support (MTSS) without
8 requiring direct surveillance of students. Funding may cover the
9 cost of software, equipment, materials, personnel, and any other
10 start-up costs of developing the pilot program. Programs may
11 involve entire districts, combinations of districts, combinations of
12 schools, or elements of schools individually or in combination.
13 B. The Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
14 Services, in cooperation with the Oklahoma State Department of
15 Education, shall determine pilot program criteria and establish a
16 process for the consideration of proposals. Such proposals for
17 pilot programs shall be considered on a statewide competitive basis.
18 C. The Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
19 Services and the State Board of Education shall each have the
20 authority to require termination of a pilot program or its
21 continuation at any time that it finds such termination to be in the
22 best interests of the students involved.
